{"TopicId":215951,"ForumId":197,"TopicTitle":"[0.1.1.0] Rover unexpected rotation after time acceleration with SAS on (video)","CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T20:48:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T20:48:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/B4G_4zFyfBo?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 Bug: Rotation after warp with SAS on\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I drived rover on Duna, I got this bug: when I turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and do time acceleration, my craft starts to rotate unpredictably. With \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E turned off bug disappears. Version of game 0.1.1.0, Windows 10 system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Little 908","CreatedById":228185,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T21:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould be a problem with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E using the reaction wheel, which usually means the reaction wheel is oriented\u00A0 wrong, this might be a bug as well.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-26T21:12:14Z\u0022 title=\u002203/26/2023 09:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Little 908\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}